<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-098-708  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 098 708.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Jan 29 1990 v36 n1794 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NSC would ease exports to East Europe; report DOD, Commerce fightgrowing. (National Security Council)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Defense and Commerce Departments are engaged in a dispute overthe relaxation of controls on the export of computers to thenewly-formed Eastern-bloc governments.andP;  The White House NationalSecurity Council has endorsed the loosening of export restrictionsin principle, but Defense and Commerce remain deadlocked over theprecise levels of computer and communication equipment that willbe allowed into Eastern Europe.andP;  Trade associations are draftingproposed standards, which the US must submit to the Free WorldCoordinating Committee (CoCom) meeting in Feb 1990.andP;  Hard-linersin the Defense Department oppose liberalization of controlsdespite the fact that many Eastern European nations have movedtoward free elections.andP;  Industry groups and the CommerceDepartment point to the relatively high Chinese export limits,noting that China currently has a more repressive government.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ComputersEastern EuropeGovernment RegulationInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>